# ============================================================
# ACTIVITY DETAIL OPERATIONS
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: operations
domain: detail
subdomain: activity-detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines operational handling for activity detail.

scope:
Covers activity-detail revision, readiness review,
blocked-state inspection, completion-rule maintenance,
and containment of unsafe operational guidance.

required_behavior:
- Support activity-detail revision.
- Support blocked-state review.
- Support operational guidance consistency checks.
- Support pause/resume rule inspection.
- Support containment of unsafe execution guidance.

state_model:
activity_detail_operational_state:
- prepared
- reviewed
- active
- paused
- blocked
- archived
- contained

validation_rules:
- activity_ref is required.
- actor and trigger semantics must remain defined.
- blocked-state guidance must include a blocking reason.
- activity detail must not redefine canonical flow order.

transition_rules:
- prepared -> reviewed
- reviewed -> active
- active -> paused
- paused -> active
- active -> blocked
- blocked -> active
- active -> archived
- active -> contained
- contained -> blocked

operational_focus:
- requirement review
- block-reason inspection
- completion-rule maintenance
- execution-guidance containment

failure_codes:
- ACTIVITY_DETAIL_OP_REF_MISSING
- ACTIVITY_DETAIL_OP_TRIGGER_INVALID
- ACTIVITY_DETAIL_OP_BLOCK_REASON_MISSING
- ACTIVITY_DETAIL_OP_FLOW_OVERRIDE_DENIED
